      "index": "aA",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1011,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 11,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "PASS 2 — UML Relationships  (drawing arrows exposes the gaps)\nATM  has-a -> AtmInventory, BankingService, IAtmState(current), Card(session)\nIAtmState <|- AAtmState(abstract, default reject) <|- Idle/CardInserted/PinEntered\nAAtmState  --back-reference-->  ATM      <-- the arrow Pass 1 missed!\n\nTWO QUESTIONS UML FORCES:\n  1) How does a state act?  -> needs a ref to ATM (constructor injection)\n  2) Who is stateful?  -> CONTEXT (ATM) holds data; STATES hold behavior only.\n     pinAttempts / currentCard MUST live on ATM (survive transitions).",
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "PASS 2 — UML Relationships  (drawing arrows exposes the gaps)\nATM  has-a -> AtmInventory, BankingService, IAtmState(current), Card(session)\nIAtmState <|- AAtmState(abstract, default reject) <|- Idle/CardInserted/PinEntered\nAAtmState  --back-reference-->  ATM      <-- the arrow Pass 1 missed!\n\nTWO QUESTIONS UML FORCES:\n  1) How does a state act?  -> needs a ref to ATM (constructor injection)\n  2) Who is stateful?  -> CONTEXT (ATM) holds data; STATES hold behavior only.\n     pinAttempts / currentCard MUST live on ATM (survive transitions).",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },

