    {
      "id": "confined-text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1300,
      "y": 120,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 690,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#c2255c",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1020,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 20,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "⭐ STAY CONFINED (scope discipline)\n\nYou fail LLD by WANDERING, not by\nbad design. 45 min → build the\nsmallest CORRECT model, nothing more.\n\nRABBIT HOLES → DISCIPLINED REPLY\n\n• Model keypad/printer/screen?\n  → No. Model behavior, not hardware.\n\n• Add Transaction hierarchy?\n  → Only if >=3 ops AND they'll grow.\n\n• Real DB / persistence?\n  → No. In-memory BankingService.\n\n• Multi-currency / cheques?\n  → Out of scope. Say it, move on.\n\n• Full Strategy for dispensing?\n  → One greedy method. Note Strategy\n    as a FUTURE extension only.\n\nTHREE PHRASES THAT SAVE YOU\n1. \"I'll assume X — fair scope?\"\n2. \"Valid extension; I'll note it and\n    keep the core first.\"\n3. \"Simpler is enough here; here's\n    when I'd upgrade it.\"\n\nRULE: every class must trace to a\nWRITTEN requirement. If it can't,\ndelete it. Design = what you leave out.",
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "⭐ STAY CONFINED (scope discipline)\n\nYou fail LLD by WANDERING, not by\nbad design. 45 min → build the\nsmallest CORRECT model, nothing more.\n\nRABBIT HOLES → DISCIPLINED REPLY\n\n• Model keypad/printer/screen?\n  → No. Model behavior, not hardware.\n\n• Add Transaction hierarchy?\n  → Only if >=3 ops AND they'll grow.\n\n• Real DB / persistence?\n  → No. In-memory BankingService.\n\n• Multi-currency / cheques?\n  → Out of scope. Say it, move on.\n\n• Full Strategy for dispensing?\n  → One greedy method. Note Strategy\n    as a FUTURE extension only.\n\nTHREE PHRASES THAT SAVE YOU\n1. \"I'll assume X — fair scope?\"\n2. \"Valid extension; I'll note it and\n    keep the core first.\"\n3. \"Simpler is enough here; here's\n    when I'd upgrade it.\"\n\nRULE: every class must trace to a\nWRITTEN requirement. If it can't,\ndelete it. Design = what you leave out.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
