      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aL",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1022,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 22,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "⌨ MACHINE CODING ROUND\n\nCODE is the score. UML often CUT.\n=> Pass 2 (relationships) moves into\n   your HEAD / rough sheet, not a diagram.\nA pretty diagram scores 0 if main\ndoesn't run. The rough pass now carries\nthe weight of TWO passes.\n\nROUGH-PASS CHECKLIST (from memory)\n1  Ownership: who holds whom?\n2  Back-refs: child needs parent?\n3  Who is STATEFUL? (the context!)\n4  Who mutates what? (point of no return)\n5  Op ordering: reversible checks FIRST\n6  Extension points: what will change?\n\nHOW TO GET BETTER\n• Skeleton-first: signatures that COMPILE,\n  then fill bodies (front-load Pass 2).\n• Reverse-check vs the 6 questions.\n• Time-box 90 min — the constraint IS\n  the skill.\n• Redo a problem 2-3x → pattern becomes\n  reflex (State = ATM/vending/elevator).\n• Runnable main (happy + 1 failure path)\n  = PROOF the wiring is correct.\n\nRULE: get to a COMPILING skeleton fast,\nthen flesh out. Never leave it all\nuncompiled until the final minute.",
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "⌨ MACHINE CODING ROUND\n\nCODE is the score. UML often CUT.\n=> Pass 2 (relationships) moves into\n   your HEAD / rough sheet, not a diagram.\nA pretty diagram scores 0 if main\ndoesn't run. The rough pass now carries\nthe weight of TWO passes.\n\nROUGH-PASS CHECKLIST (from memory)\n1  Ownership: who holds whom?\n2  Back-refs: child needs parent?\n3  Who is STATEFUL? (the context!)\n4  Who mutates what? (point of no return)\n5  Op ordering: reversible checks FIRST\n6  Extension points: what will change?\n\nHOW TO GET BETTER\n• Skeleton-first: signatures that COMPILE,\n  then fill bodies (front-load Pass 2).\n• Reverse-check vs the 6 questions.\n• Time-box 90 min — the constraint IS\n  the skill.\n• Redo a problem 2-3x → pattern becomes\n  reflex (State = ATM/vending/elevator).\n• Runnable main (happy + 1 failure path)\n  = PROOF the wiring is correct.\n\nRULE: get to a COMPILING skeleton fast,\nthen flesh out. Never leave it all\nuncompiled until the final minute.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
